    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-09-07T04:11:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-09-07T04:11:00-05:00" n="939"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d939">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795B.5/9–754: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief, Far East (<persName corresp="#p_HGJE1"
                            type="from">Hull</persName>) to the Chief of Staff, United States Army
                            (<persName corresp="#p_RGMB1" type="to">Ridgway</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-09-07T18:11:00+09:00"
                            >September 7, 1954—6:11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>C 69527. From <gloss target="#t_CINCFE1">CINCFE</gloss> to <gloss
                        target="#t_DEPTAR1">DeptAr</gloss> info CGArmyEight. <gloss target="#t_DA1"
                        >DA</gloss> exclusive for <persName corresp="#p_RGMB1">Ridgway</persName>
                    from <persName corresp="#p_HGJE1">Hull</persName>. Army Eight exclusive for
                        <persName corresp="#p_TLGMD1">Taylor</persName> from <pb facs="0755"
                        n="1873" xml:id="pg_1873"/>
                    <persName corresp="#p_HGJE1">Hull</persName>. <gloss target="#t_DEPTAR1"
                        >DeptAr</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_OCS1">OCS</gloss> now repeats for info State Department
                    exclusive for <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName>.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_TLGMD1">Taylor</persName> informs me that Secretary
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> has queried Ambassador
                        <persName corresp="#p_BEO1">Briggs</persName> concerning <gloss
                        target="#t_ROKA1">ROKA</gloss> planning for possible unilateral military
                    action.</p>
                <p>It has been reasonably clear for some time that on President <persName
                        corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName>’s orders <gloss target="#t_ROKA1"
                        >ROKA</gloss> staff is working on plans for unilateral military action. Fact
                    that such planning goes on is not particularly disturbing providing responsible
                    senior commanders do not delude themselves as to practicability of such plans.
                    To preclude this latter possibility, <persName corresp="#p_TLGMD1"
                        >Taylor</persName>, with my express approval, has taken advantage of recent
                    opportunities to emphasize to senior <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss>
                    Generals that US will not support in any way reopening of hostilities by <gloss
                        target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss>; furthermore, that we will not be deceived by
                    any incident designed cast blame on Communists. As I had opportunity during past
                    week in conversation with General <persName corresp="#p_YPSLBS1">Lee</persName>,
                    Chairman <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss>, and General <persName corresp="#p_CCW1"
                        >Chung</persName>, <gloss target="#t_COFS1">COFS</gloss> of <gloss
                        target="#t_ROKA1">ROKA</gloss>, I made point of informing them along similar
                    lines.</p>
                <p>All US authorities in Korea are watching vigilantly for any indications of <gloss
                        target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> future intentions.</p>
                <p>You may wish to pass above information to other members <gloss target="#t_JCS1"
                        >JCS</gloss> and top level State Department officials.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
